<ARCH_SCAN_V3>
@ID: DATA_IN_TRANSIT_AUDIT
@GOAL: VERIFY_TRANSPORT_LAYER_SECURITY_AND_ENCRYPTION_FOR_ALL_COMMUNICATION_CHANNELS
@PARENT_CONTEXT: protocol_discovery.protocol, outbound_trust.protocol

<GLOBAL_VARS>
# Требования к шифрованию каналов
INSECURE_TRANSIT: "(http://|ws://|ftp://|telnet://|smtp://|!tls)"
SECURE_TLS: "(TLS_1.2|TLS_1.3|https://|wss://)"

# Маркеры конфигурации TLS/SSL
TLS_CONFIG: "(rejectUnauthorized|ca|cert|key|ciphers|minVersion|secureOptions)"
SECURITY_HEADERS: "(Strict-Transport-Security|X-Content-Type-Options)"
</GLOBAL_VARS>

<CONTEXT_MAP>
[EGRESS_POINT]  <- {match: {{OUTBOUND_CLIENTS}}, scope: "FUNCTION_CALL"}
[SERVER_CONFIG] <- {match: (https\.createServer|tls\.createServer|app\.listen|ssl_certificate), scope: "BOOTSTRAP"}
[INTERNAL_COMM] <- {match: (grpc|amqp|redis|mongodb), context: "connection_string"}
</CONTEXT_MAP>

<ASSERTIONS>
# Логические инварианты передачи данных
! (ANY -> {{INSECURE_TRANSIT}}) : "CRITICAL: Plaintext communication detected. Data is vulnerable to sniffing and MitM attacks."
! ([SERVER_CONFIG]) & !Strict-Transport-Security : "HIGH: HSTS header missing. Risk of protocol downgrade attacks (SSLStrip)."
? (rejectUnauthorized: false) : "CRITICAL: Certificate validation is disabled. System will trust any malicious certificate (Perfect MitM)."
! (ZONE_INT -> ZONE_SEC) & !{{SECURE_TLS}} : "MEDIUM: Internal 'East-West' traffic is unencrypted. Risk of lateral movement sniffing."
</ASSERTIONS>

<EXECUTION_PIPELINE>
1. TRANSPORT_STACK_SCAN:
   - Identify all [EGRESS_POINT] and [INTERNAL_COMM] URLs.
   - Flag any use of non-TLS protocols (HTTP/WS/FTP) in any environment except 'local-dev'.
2. CERTIFICATE_VALIDATION_AUDIT:
   - Search for `rejectUnauthorized: false` or `NODE_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=0`.
   - Verify if custom CA bundles are correctly loaded for internal services.
3. HSTS_AND_REDIRECT_CHECK:
   - Check if the server forces HTTPS and sends the `Strict-Transport-Security` header.
   - Verify if `301 Redirect` from HTTP to HTTPS is implemented.
4. WEAK_CIPHER_DETECTION:
   - Analyze [SERVER_CONFIG] for allowed TLS versions and cipher suites.
   - Flag deprecated versions (TLS 1.0/1.1) or weak ciphers (RC4, DES).
5. MAN_IN_THE_MIDDLE_SURFACE:
   - Check for sensitive data (from data_inventory.protocol) being sent in URL Query Params (where it's visible to proxies/logs).
</EXECUTION_PIPELINE>

<OUTPUT_SPEC>
GENERATE_TRANSIT_SECURITY_REPORT:
  - CHANNEL_NAME | PROTOCOL | ENCRYPTION_TYPE | CERT_VALIDATION | RISK_LEVEL
VISUALIZE: "Mermaid graph: use Solid Green lines for TLS and Red Dashed lines for Plaintext."
FILTER: RISK >= MEDIUM
</OUTPUT_SPEC>
</ARCH_SCAN_V3>